{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f96e4e0c-0cc0-4628-84c9-12378148492c","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run `dotnet restore` to pull updated packages, and `dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Check for any NuGet packages with explicit 10.x versions (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) and bump those to their 11.x equivalents.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9b096ddd-d13e-4f4f-8aab-4e4909cf5266","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the files involved.","outputTokens":285},"id":"f5b3d3f6-b4ae-4763-b577-63edff9cdbc5","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:59:08.507Z","parentId":"bed0e140-87d5-4f2a-92e5-6d724af3fe97"}
